  "description": "Run lifecycle / traceability. Pair with docs/runbooks/TRACE_A_RUN.md. Trace viewer URL uses API run.otelTraceId + NEXT_PUBLIC_TRACE_VIEWER_URL_TEMPLATE (not this dashboard).",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 0,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "liveNow": false,
  "panels": [
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "id": 10,
      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "## Trace viewer\n\n1. `GET /v1/architecture/run/$runId` → copy **`run.otelTraceId`**.\n2. Open your trace UI with that **32-char hex** (same `{traceId}` placeholder as operator UI / CLI `ARCHLUCID_TRACE_VIEWER_URL_TEMPLATE`).\n\nExample: `[Open trace](${TRACE_VIEWER_BASE:raw}/$runId)` — replace **`TRACE_VIEWER_BASE`** with your Grafana Explore or Jaeger base (Grafana variables cannot substitute API responses; use the runbook for the exact URL).",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Trace viewer link (manual)",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "description": "Durable audit lives in SQL. Grafana needs a SQL datasource or use the API: `GET /v1/audit/search?runId=$runId&take=500`.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 4 },
      "id": 11,
      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "| Step | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| By run | `GET /v1/audit/search?runId=**$runId**&take=500` |\n| By correlation | After first response, `GET /v1/audit/search?correlationId=...` |\n\nIndex: **IX_AuditEvents_RunId_OccurredUtc** (migration 055).",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Run audit timeline (API)",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 4 },
      "id": 12,
      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "**No SQL datasource** in the default ArchLucid Grafana bundle. Use **`GET /v1/audit/search`** (see left panel) or add a Grafana SQL datasource to `dbo.AuditEvents` in your environment.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Audit SQL note",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "ms" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 9 },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum(rate(archlucid_authority_pipeline_stage_duration_ms_bucket{stage=~\"context_ingestion|graph|findings|decisioning|artifacts\"}[5m])) by (le, stage))",
          "legendFormat": "{{stage}} p95",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Authority pipeline stage duration (p95, all runs)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "description": "Per-run label filtering requires OTel → Prometheus to expose archlucid.run_id on histograms; when absent, this shows global throughput.",
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": {}, "overrides": [] },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 9 },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum(rate(archlucid_llm_calls_per_run_bucket[5m])) by (le))",
          "legendFormat": "p95 calls/run (global)",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "LLM calls per run (p95, global)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": {}, "overrides": [] },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 17 },
      "id": 3,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(archlucid_circuit_breaker_state_transitions_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "state transitions/s",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(archlucid_circuit_breaker_rejections_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "rejections/s",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Circuit breaker (global rates)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    }
  ],
